# AI
- All AI goes through the `AIProvider` interface (generateSummary, extractMetadata, generateTags, detectDuplicates, clusterEvents, translate, summarizeDaily). NEVER call Gemini or any LLM SDK directly from features.
- First implementation: `GeminiFlashProvider`. Providers must be swappable without touching feature code.
- Validate every provider output with Zod; on malformed output, retry once then mark the job `error`.
- The pipeline writes DRAFTS only (`status = needs_review`). It never publishes. People are proposed and default to `redacted`.
- Send only already-public content to the model; never submitter PII. Respect batch/rate limits (free tier).
- The platform must work if AI is disabled — guard AI paths behind a flag.
